If compiling with API level 21+, then it will cause link error that `bsd_signal` is missing if uses libwebsockets. It is because libwebsockets used `signal()`, and on Android 19 or lower version, `signal` is implemented as(can refer to `NDK_ROOT/platforms/android-19/arch-arm/usr/include/signal.h`)

``` c++
static __inline__ __sighandler_t signal(int s, __sighandler_t f)
{
    return bsd_signal(s,f);
}
```

But `bsd_signal` is removed with 21+. There is also [an issue](https://github.com/android-ndk/ndk/issues/160) in `android-ndk`. It seems it will be fixed in NDK r13.

